<topic id="dita-profile-content">
  <title>Creating and Editing Profiling Attributes in DITA</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>DITA<indexterm>Profiling<indexterm>Creating or editing profiling
              attributes</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>You can filter DITA content or the structure of a document by using profiling attributes or
        <xref href="dita-condition-sets-management.dita#dita-condition-sets-management">profiling
        conditions sets</xref>.</p>
    <section id="define-profiling-attributes">
      <title>Defining Profiling Attributes for DITA Content</title>
      <p>To create or edit profiling attributes for filtering DITA content, follow these steps:<ol>
          <li><ph conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/ph-step1"/><note type="tip">For less
              technical users who do not want to create attribute specializations in DTD/XML Schema,
              you may want to use <xref href="dita-profiling-attribute-groups.dita">profiling
                attribute groups</xref> instead (use an existing profiling attribute with
              sub-attributes).</note></li>
          <li><ph conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/Open-the-preferences-page"/> and go to <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Edit modes</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Profiling / Conditional Text</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Attributes and Condition Sets</uicontrol>
            </menucascade>.<note type="other" othertype="Information">The <xref
                href="preferences-attributes-and-condition-sets.dita#preferences-attributes-and-condition-sets/profiling-attributes-section"
                  ><uicontrol>Profiling Attributes</uicontrol> section</xref> is used to define the
              attributes and their values. For DITA documents, the default attributes are included
                (<xmlatt>audience</xmlatt>, <xmlatt>platform</xmlatt>, <xmlatt>product</xmlatt>,
                <xmlatt>props</xmlatt>, <xmlatt>otherprops</xmlatt>, and <xmlatt>rev</xmlatt>), but
              if a <xref href="../topics/subject-scheme-map.dita#subject-scheme-map"><term>Subject
                  Scheme Map</term></xref> is used for profiling your content, you will see the
              attributes defined in your <term>subject scheme map</term> instead.</note></li>
          <li>
            <p><ph conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/ph-for-DITA-1"/></p>
            <p conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/p-for-DITA-1"/>
            <p conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/p-for-DITA-2"/>
            <p conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/p-for-DITA-p3"/>
            <p><ph conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/ph-for-DITA-2"/><dl>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/dlentry-for-DITA-1">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/dlentry-for-DITA-2">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/dlentry-for-DITA-3">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="attr-values-table">
                  <dt>Attribute Values Table</dt>
                  <dd>
                    <p>This table displays information about the values for the profiling attribute.
                      You can configure them by using the buttons at the bottom of the table
                        (<uicontrol product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"><image
                          href="../img/Add16.png" id="image_um5_3c1_x3b"/>New</uicontrol><uicontrol
                        product="author editor">New</uicontrol>, <uicontrol><image
                          href="../img/Wrench16.png" product="authorEclipse editorEclipse"
                          id="image_vm5_3c1_x3b"/>Edit</uicontrol>, <uicontrol><image
                          href="../img/RemoveSelected16.gif" placement="inline"
                          product="authorEclipse editorEclipse" id="image_wm5_3c1_x3b"
                        />Delete</uicontrol>).</p>
                    <p>The columns are as follows:<ul irina="irina">
                        <li><uicontrol>Value</uicontrol> - The attribute value. You can also define
                          profiling attribute groups using the following format:
                            <codeph>ParentAttrValue(SubAttrValue1 SubAttrValue2)</codeph>. For more
                          information, see <xref href="dita-profiling-attribute-groups.dita"/>.</li>
                        <li><uicontrol>Label</uicontrol> - You can specify a label for the attribute
                          value that will be rendered as its name in various components in
                            <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode (<xref
                            href="dita-apply-profiling-attributes.dita#dita-apply-profiling-attributes"
                              ><uicontrol>Edit Profiling Attributes</uicontrol> dialog box</xref>,
                            <xref
                            href="dita-condition-sets-management.dita#dita-condition-sets-management"
                              ><uicontrol>Condition Set</uicontrol> dialog box</xref>, <xref
                            href="dita-edit-properties.dita#dita-edit-properties/profiling_tab"
                              ><uicontrol>Profiling</uicontrol> tab in the <uicontrol>Edit
                              Properties</uicontrol> dialog box</xref>, <xref
                            href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
                              Manager</uicontrol></xref>). If the <uicontrol>Label</uicontrol> is
                          not specified, the <uicontrol>Value</uicontrol> will be used as its
                          rendered name.</li>
                        <li><uicontrol>Description</uicontrol> - A description for the attribute
                          value that will be displayed in this table.</li>
                      </ul></p>
                  </dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/dlentry-for-DITA-5">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/dlentry-for-DITA-6">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl></p>
          </li>
          <li conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/profiling-li-3"/>
          <li conkeyref="reusables-author-for-dita/profiling-li-4"/>
        </ol></p>
      <p><b>Result:</b> You should see your changes in the <uicontrol>Profiling
          Attribute</uicontrol> table.</p>
      <p>You can also use the <uicontrol>Profiling Condition Sets</uicontrol> section to apply more
        complex filters on your DITA content.</p>
    </section>
